```To use the !addcommand function you have to have at least one name to do that you do the following: 
 !addcommand names: This is one name, anotherName 
That will create a empty command that will do nothing. 

 If you want the bot to send a message when someone types a name of a command you do this:
  !addcommand names: name message: This will be the message    This will send the message "This will be the message" when ever someone types "name" into chat.  

  If you would also like it to react to the user who sent the message you do the following
    !addcommand names: name emotes: sunglasses heart (any normal emotes will work just remove the : )   

 If you want the bot to send a image with a command you drag the image over to discord and then were it says   
add comment you do the !addcommand with what ever you want.   

 If you want a command like the AAAAAAAA command all you have to do is the following  
  !addcommand names: AAAA message: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y4Z7Ds_yv8o exact: falseWhat that does is let the word be in another word or as in this case let it be a bunch of a's minim of 4. 

 To remove a command all you have to do is type : !removecommand name```
